'Biology' is a natural science concerned with the study of life and living
organisms, including their structure, function, growth, evolution, distribution,
and taxonomy.<ref>Based on definition from
[http://www.bio.txstate.edu/~wetlands/Glossary/glossary.html Aquarena Wetlands
Project glossary of terms.]</ref> Modern biology is composed of many
subdisciplines unified by five so-called axioms:<ref name="avila_biology"></ref>

# Cells are the basic unit of life Genes are the basic unit of heredity New
# species and inherited traits are the product of evolution An organism
# regulates its internal environment to maintain a stable and constant condition
# Living organisms consume and transform energy

Subdisciplines of biology are defined by the scale at which organisms are
studied and the methods used to study them: biochemistry examines the
rudimentary chemistry of life; molecular biology studies the complex
interactions among biological molecules; cellular biology examines the basic
building block of all life, the cell; physiology examines the physical and
chemical functions of tissues, organs, and organ systems of an organism;
evolutionary biology examines the processes that produced the diversity of life;
and ecology examines how organisms interact in their
